Sematic Versioning - https://semver.org/

Install express : npm install express --save
Install nodemon with dev dependancies : npm install nodemon --save-dev

Why ~ and ^ used in package versions :
    Eg: "nodemon": "^2.0.4"
    ~ compatible with future patches
    ^ compatible with future minor/patches
        Reference :
            https://stackoverflow.com/questions/22343224/whats-the-difference-between-tilde-and-caret-in-package-json#:~:text=npm%20checks%20and%20fixes%20the,fixed%2C%20matches%20any%20build%20number

Get the latest version of any package : 
    npm i express@latest --save (--save makes an entry in the package.json)

Get outdates packag details : 
    npm outdated

How to seperate dev and prod env :
    Run start script : npm start
    Run dev script : npm run dev (check package.json for more details)

